  passAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 42294c6386e8aee43b693b0ad2a35365, type: 3}
  textBox: {fileID: 2116495422}
  dialogueText: 'But I, although I had seen and heard these things, nevertheless
    because of the doubt and bad opinion and divers remarks of men, refused for a
    long time the duty of writing, not in obstinacy but in humility, until I fell
    on a bed of sickness, cast down by the scourge of God, until at length I was
    compelled to write by many infirmities.


    -Hildelgard of Bingen''s.'
